<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Violation: el_size is computed by adding hdr->header_size, hdr->value_size and several small constants into a size_t. These additions can overflow (wrap-around). Example: if hdr->header_size = SIZE_MAX - 3 and hdr->value_size = 0 then el_size becomes (SIZE_MAX - 3) + 2 + 0 + 2 = SIZE_MAX + 1 -> wraps to 0. The subsequent check if (buf_size < *ppos + el_size) can therefore pass incorrectly and the following memcpy calls (which copy hdr->header_size and hdr->value_size bytes) will write beyond buf bounds. Thus Rule 21.17 is violated.
</scenario>

